      </div>

      <div id="balance-check" class="balance-check balanced">✅ The balance sheet balances! Assets = Liabilities + Equity</div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ CHARTS ═══ -->
    <h2 id="balance-sheet-charts">Balance Sheet Breakdown: Charts</h2>
    <p>Visual breakdowns of <strong>TechCorp Inc.'s</strong> balance sheet help you quickly understand the composition of assets and the funding structure.</p>

    <div class="chart-grid">
      <div class="chart-container">
        <h3 style="text-align:center;color:#c8d0de;margin:0 0 12px">Stacked Bar: Assets vs Liabilities+Equity</h3>
        <canvas id="stackedBarChart" width="500" height="350"></canvas>
      </div>
      <div class="chart-container">
        <h3 style="text-align:center;color:#c8d0de;margin:0 0 12px">Asset Composition (Doughnut)</h3>
